Hilton Worldwide Holdings: A Leader in the Hotels, Restaurants & Leisure Sector

As ranked 389th in the Fortune 2024 list, Hilton Worldwide Holdings has demonstrated its resilience and growth in the competitive Hotels, Restaurants & Leisure sector. With a market value of $53.788 billion as of March 28, 2024, the company has not only maintained its position but has also shown a remarkable improvement in its ranking, jumping 42 positions since the previous year.

Under the leadership of CEO Christopher J. Nassetta, Hilton Worldwide Holdings has continued to thrive, with revenues reaching $10.235 billion, a 16.7% increase from the previous year. However, the company's profits experienced a decline of 9.1%, totaling $1.141 billion. Despite this, Hilton remains a profitable entity, with a strong asset base of $15.401 billion.

The company's growth is also reflected in its employee base, with a workforce of 178,000 individuals globally. This growth in jobs is a testament to Hilton's commitment to expanding its operations and creating opportunities for its employees.

Hilton Worldwide Holdings is a well-established player in the industry, with a long history of excellence. The company's inclusion in the World's Most Admired Companies and Best Companies to Work For lists is a reflection of its commitment to quality, innovation, and employee satisfaction.

As a public company, Hilton is listed on the stock exchange under the ticker symbol HLT. Headquartered in McLean, Virginia, the company operates globally, with a strong presence in the U.S. and international markets.

In recognition of its achievements, Hilton Worldwide Holdings has been included in the World's Most Admired Companies list, a testament to its reputation and standing in the industry. The company's commitment to excellence and its dedication to its employees have also earned it a place in the Best Companies to Work For list.

As the company continues to grow and expand its operations, it remains focused on delivering exceptional service and experiences to its customers. With its strong brand reputation and commitment to excellence, Hilton Worldwide Holdings is well-positioned for continued success in the Hotels, Restaurants & Leisure sector.

For more information about Hilton Worldwide Holdings, please visit their website at https://www.hilton.com.